-- Spanish Candidate May Head ESM, Mersch for ECB Seat: AFP
-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 2012-03-25T09:44:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/spanish-candidate-may-head-esm-mersch-for-ecb-seat-afp.html
A Spanish candidate may be
appointed at the helm of the European Stability Mechanism and
Luxembourg’s Yves Mersch may in turn get a seat on the  European
Central Bank ’s board, Agence France-Presse reported, citing an
unidentified European official.  Germany ’s Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  is the most
likely candidate to win the Eurogroup presidency to succeed
Jean-Claude Juncker, AFP said, citing another unidentified
European official. AFP was reporting from a European meeting in
 Finland .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helene Fouquet in Paris at 
